wikipedia_page.main: Katherine Mary Brown (born 24 January 1953) is an English former cricketer who played as a right-arm off break bowling all-rounder. She appeared in 1 Test match and 2 One Day Internationals for England between 1976 and 1979, as well as playing 3 matches for Young England at the 1973 World Cup. She played domestic cricket for Kent.
